The paper proposes a deep learning method for object saliency detection using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The method involves using a gradient descent method to modify input images based on pixel-wise gradients, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of SLIC superpixels and LAB color-based low-level saliency features, which are techniques commonly used in image retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM). Overall, the paper's focus on deep learning and computer vision suggests that cs.CV is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.AI and cs.LG. The use of low-level features and image retrieval techniques suggests cs.IR and cs.MM as possible sub-categories as well.
